# Personal Portfolio — Cursor context

## Stack
- Next.js (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- Import alias: `@/*` maps to `./src/*`

## Folder conventions
- `src/app/` — routes, layout, global styles
- `src/components/` — UI sections and reusable pieces (Hero, About, Work, Contact, etc.)
- `src/lib/` — small helpers, constants, shared utilities

## How to build features
- Use the **user’s stated copy and goals** from the chat (name, tagline, projects, contact) when implementing UI; if something is missing, ask briefly before inventing personal details.
- Build the single-page portfolio **one section at a time** (start with Hero), then iterate.
- Use Tailwind for styling; keep layouts **responsive** (mobile-first, sensible breakpoints).
- Prefer accessible HTML (semantic landmarks, labels on form controls when you add the Contact section).

## Out of scope until requested
- Do not add dark mode, smooth scroll, or load animations unless the user asks (stretch goals).
